UoPeople Clock (GMT-5)

All activities close on Wednesdays at 11:55 PM, except for Learning Journals/Portfolios which close on Thursdays at 11:55 PM. Always follow the clock at the top of the page.

Due dates/times displayed in activities will vary based on your time zone, however you are still required to follow the 11:55 PM GMT-5 deadline.

Reading Assignment

Illowsky, B., Dean, S., Birmajer, D., Blount, B., Boyd, S., Einsohn, M., Helmreich, Kenyon, L., Lee, S., & Taub, J. (2022). Introductory statistics. openstax. https://openstax.org/details/books/introductory-statistics

    • To get started, thoroughly read the Syllabus for this course accessible on the course homepage in the General Information section.
    • View the online book.
    • Read Chapter 4 - Discrete Random Variables 
      • Section 4.1 - Probabality distribution function 
      • Section 4.2 - Mean or expected value and standard deviation 
      • Section 4.3 - Binomial distribution
    • Solve the following practice exercises as homework from the attached Practice Exercise-Unit 4.pdf

Videos:

Grant, C. M. (2022, January 23). 4.1 Probability distribution function PDF for a discrete random variable [Video]. YouTube.

    • This video introduces the probability distribution of discrete random variable.

Grant, C. M.  (2022b, January 24). 4.2 Mean or expected value and standard deviation [Video]. YouTube.

    • This video introduces the concept of expected value and the standard deviation in the context of a random variable
